Write a program that asks a user for the name of an item and its price and stores this information in 2 separate variables. 

The item name must be a String 

The price must be a Float 

Calculate a 10% discount (Price multiplied by 0.9) and print: "The new price for [item] is [discounted price]", where ‘[item]’ and ‘[discounted price]’ is where you reference your variables. 

 

Answer: 
item = input("enter a name of an item")
price = float(input("enter the price of the item must be a decimal number"))
new_price = price * 0.9
print("the new price for {} is {}".format(item, new_price))

 

 

 

 
